title: Presidents Cup 2015: What time do singles matches start for Jordan Spieth, Phil Mickelson and others?
text:
Comments 
The United States -- expected to romp in the Presidents Cup -- is in a street fight with a feisty International squad. 
The Americans will hold just a one point lead, 9.5-8.5, when the teams tee off Sunday in Incheon City, South Korea (that's Saturday night Eastern time) in 12 singles matches that will decide the event. 
Television coverage information is here. 
The Americans opened with a 4-1 lead Thursday and have been outplayed — but not my much — ever since. 
"To me, it kind of feels like we're losing just because of what's gone on the last two days," Zach Johnson said. "But our first day was substantial. So yeah, you knew it was going to be tight going into Sunday regardless of what happened." 
The first match goes off at 8:15 p.m. Eastern, with TV coverage beginning at 9:30 p.m. Eastern. 
Here's a look at the pairings: At Jack Nicklaus Golf Club Korea Incheon, South Korea
